-- MOVES-Bessemer Trust makes appointments to wealth management team
-- By Anannya Pramanick in Bangalore
-- Mon Nov 17, 2014 01:15PM EST
-- None



Nov 17 (Reuters) - Private wealth management and investment advisory firm Bessemer Trust made two appointments to its wealth management team.

The firm appointed Grant Gardner as principal, head of estate administration and fiduciary counsel. Gardner will be based in Bessemer's New York office and will be responsible for managing all estates for which Bessemer is serving as executor or as personal representative.   The firm also appointed Steven Dwyer as senior vice president and real estate asset manager. Dwyer will be based in  Los Angeles.